snippet.title: Eternal Destiny - Gameplay
snippet.description:
Part of my Obscure First Person Shooters series: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL2BBA1AB1CF53EEAC

Gameplay footage from Eternal Destiny, a landmark title in that it holds the dubious honor of being the first and only first person shooter built natively for Acorn's RiscPC machine. It's also British.

For reference purposes:
http://web.archive.org/web/20050829032809/http://come.to/eternal-destiny
http://www.acorn-gaming.org.uk/index.php3?p=Reviews/Destiny/index
http://www.acornarcade.com/forums/viewthread.php?newsid=1043
http://gnuart.net/galerie.php?path=data/musique/mirko_vidovic/eternal_destiny

Note: I apologize for having to record the "pre-prerelease demo". It is surprisingly difficult to track down a retail CD copy of a game developed for an already-antiquated computer system that was only sold direct from the developer (for £35!) shipped from Manchester during a short period in the late 90s. To make up for this, I'm doing a dual obscure FPS video release. I'm writing this weeks after recording the previous video, so I hope that last one was good.
